## The Step-Cut Tennis Difference

The single most important fact about the emerald cut tennis necklace: it looks nothing like a brilliant-cut tennis necklace. These are different objects that produce different effects.

A brilliant-cut tennis creates omnidirectional sparkle. Every stone scatters light in all directions at once. The necklace glitters continuously from any angle, in any light. This is the image most buyers have when they hear "diamond tennis necklace."

An emerald cut tennis creates directional light. Each stone reflects in long horizontal bands. When you move, those bands shift in unison across the entire necklace. The effect is architectural and rolling — not a shimmer but a wave. It reads as one piece, not a collection of stones.

The per-stone size difference between CTW levels is real and visible. At 10 CTW, individual stones are approximately 0.29ct each — roughly 4.5mm × 3.3mm. At 15 CTW, approximately 0.43ct each — roughly 5.2mm × 3.8mm. At 20 CTW, roughly 0.57ct each — approximately 5.8mm × 4.2mm. The jump from 10 to 15 CTW is visible at neckline distance, both in per-stone size and in the total width of the step-cut band.

If you want a tennis necklace that glitters in a dark room, buy brilliant cut. If you want a necklace that makes a statement in daylight and reads as a single architectural surface, the [10 CTW at $15,750](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-tennis-necklace-with-10-ctw-emerald-cut-diamonds-in-14k-white-gold-item-297603?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the entry point.

---

## Emerald Cut Diamond Necklace Gold: Choosing Your Metal

Gold color changes the look of a step-cut pendant more than most buyers expect. The stone's light is white and cool. The metal creates the frame for that light.

[![East-west emerald cut bezel diamond pendant necklace in yellow gold worn model](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/LifeStyle/DiamondBasics/857142/857142_EMR_1500CT_Y_1_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-3-4-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251428?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

**White gold and platinum** let the stone dominate. The metal disappears visually. The pendant reads as a floating white architectural element against the skin. This is the most minimal and modern look — it matches white gold ring stacks without introducing warm tones.

**Yellow gold** creates deliberate contrast. The warm metal sets off the step-cut's cool white light. The result reads more like traditional fine jewelry — intentional warmth around a clean, cool stone. The [East-West Bezel in 14K Yellow Gold at $1,820](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-2-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251426?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and the white gold version at the same price let you compare the same stone in two completely different contexts.

Rose gold is not available in the emerald cut bezel pendant format in pre-made certified inventory. This is worth knowing if you are shopping with a specific metal preference — the product range covers white gold, yellow gold, and platinum only. Custom work through a jeweler can produce a rose gold east-west bezel, but lead times and pricing are different from pre-made inventory. If rose gold is your priority, the north-south solitaire format has broader custom availability.

The platinum options run $280 more at 1/2 ct. and $270 more at 1 ct. versus 14K white gold. For pendants worn daily, that is money well spent — the platinum bezel retains its shape and hardness longer than 14K gold without thinning.

[![East-west emerald cut bezel diamond pendant in white gold 2 carat lifestyle](https://ion.bluenile.com/sets/Jewelry/Photoshoot/Bluenile/LifeStyle/DiamondBasics/857142/857142_EMR_2000CT_W_2_1600X1600.jpg)](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-platinum-1-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251408?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

---

## Emerald Cut Diamond Pendant Chain Length Guide

Chain length determines where the pendant sits on the body and how visible it is in different necklines. Most buyers default to whatever chain comes with the pendant — this is a mistake worth thinking about before ordering.

**16 inches** sits at the collarbone. For an east-west pendant, this positions the horizontal stone at the base of the throat. It reads as a choker-adjacent length — modern and close to the neckline. For buyers who wear open-collar shirts or lower necklines, 16 inches works well.

**18 inches** sits mid-decolletage. This is the most common choice for an east-west pendant — it positions the horizontal stone where the chest is flattest, which is where the step-cut light is most visible from the front. Most lifestyle photos of east-west pendants use 18-inch chains.

**20 inches** drops below mid-decolletage. This works for buyers who want the pendant to sit lower or who wear higher necklines where 18 inches would disappear under fabric. The step-cut light is still visible at 20 inches but the stone is further from the viewer's sightline.

For the tennis necklace format, chain length is determined by the product — the necklace itself sits at the collarbone as a full circuit around the neck. There is no chain length decision to make for the tennis format. The circuit length is fixed and sized for a standard collarbone fit. If your neck measurement is significantly above or below average, confirm sizing before ordering — the bezel-set emerald cut tennis necklace cannot be lengthened or shortened without disassembling and reassembling the stone circuit.

