## Expert Summary

The emerald cut diamond necklace comes down to two separate buying decisions: the pendant and the tennis necklace.

For the pendant, orientation is more important than carat weight. East-west gives you the long axis at chest level, the step-cut light running parallel to the collarbone, and a bezel setting that protects the corners. North-south is the traditional format — still the right call for buyers who want that classic look. The price at any given carat is nearly identical between the two orientations. The look is completely different.

The [East-West Bezel 14K White Gold 1/2 ct. at $1,820](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-2-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251401?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the strongest value in the pendant range. The [East-West Bezel Platinum 1 ct. at $5,460](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-platinum-1-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251408?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the step-up for buyers who want real presence at the neckline. For the tennis necklace, the [10 CTW at $15,750](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-tennis-necklace-with-10-ctw-emerald-cut-diamonds-in-14k-white-gold-item-297603?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the entry point and the [15 CTW at $25,893](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-tennis-necklace-with-15-ctw-emerald-cut-diamonds-in-14k-white-gold-item-297604?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) has visibly larger individual stones.

> "I tell people: the east-west pendant is not just a trend. The orientation actually makes the stone work better at the neckline. The step-cut's best quality is those long horizontal light bands. When you hang it horizontally, you see that quality at its best. When you hang it vertically, you see the shorter width of the stone and most of the effect disappears. It is a simple choice that unlocks everything the emerald cut is good at."
>
> — Farzana, DiamondCritics

---

## Final Verdict

**Best everyday pendant:** [East-West Bezel 14K White Gold 1/2 ct. at $1,820](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-2-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251401?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Correct orientation, bezel protection, 1/2 ct. reads clearly at chest level — best price-to-presence ratio in the pendant range.

**Best for yellow gold:** [East-West Bezel 14K Yellow Gold 1/2 ct. at $1,820](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-2-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251426?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Same price as white gold, warm metal contrast against step-cut white light — more traditional look, still architectural.

**Best for durability:** [East-West Bezel Platinum 1 ct. at $5,460](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-platinum-1-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251408?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Platinum bezel at 1 ct. — the stone has real neckline presence and the platinum holds shape for decades without maintenance.

**Best statement piece:** [East-West Bezel Tennis Necklace 14K White Gold 10 CTW at $15,750](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-tennis-necklace-with-10-ctw-emerald-cut-diamonds-in-14k-white-gold-item-297603?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Entry-point to the step-cut tennis format — a continuous architectural band of light across the collarbone, nothing like a brilliant-cut tennis.

