## FAQ

### What is an emerald cut diamond necklace?

An emerald cut diamond necklace is a pendant or tennis necklace featuring one or more emerald cut diamonds — a rectangular step-cut shape with cropped corners and parallel facets that reflect light in long horizontal bands. It comes in two pendant orientations (north-south vertical and east-west horizontal) and as a full east-west bezel tennis necklace from 10 to 20 carats total weight.

### What is the difference between east-west and north-south for an emerald cut pendant?

East-west hangs the stone horizontally — the long axis runs parallel to the collarbone, presenting more visual width to the viewer and aligning the step-cut's horizontal light with the body. North-south hangs it vertically — the shorter width faces the viewer. East-west reads larger from the same carat and is the modern orientation. North-south is the classic traditional format.

### How much does an emerald cut diamond necklace cost?

Entry-level east-west bezel pendants start at [$910 for 1/4 ct.](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-4-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251398?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and reach [$5,460 for 1 ct. in platinum](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-platinum-1-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251408?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Tennis necklaces start at [$15,750 for 10 CTW in 14K gold](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-tennis-necklace-with-10-ctw-emerald-cut-diamonds-in-14k-white-gold-item-297603?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and reach [$44,617 for 20 CTW in platinum](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-tennis-necklace-with-20-ctw-emerald-cut-diamonds-in-platinum-item-297615?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational).

### What clarity should I choose for an emerald cut diamond pendant?

All pre-made emerald cut pendants in the market are H-I, SI1-SI2 clarity. At typical pendant viewing distance of 18–24 inches, SI1 inclusions are significantly less visible than on a ring. For pendants under 1/2 ct., SI1 is acceptable and a strong value. For 1 ct. pendants that will be closely inspected or photographed, SI1 is the safer grade — SI2 can tip into visible territory at that size.

### What is an emerald cut diamond tennis necklace?

An emerald cut diamond tennis necklace is a full bezel circuit of east-west set emerald cut diamonds. Unlike a brilliant-cut tennis that creates continuous sparkle, the step-cut tennis creates directional horizontal bands of light that move in unison as you move. The [10 CTW at $15,750](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-tennis-necklace-with-10-ctw-emerald-cut-diamonds-in-14k-white-gold-item-297603?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the entry point for this format.

### Should I choose 14K gold or platinum for my emerald cut diamond pendant?

For everyday wear, platinum is the better choice. The bezel wraps metal around the stone's perimeter — in platinum, that lip holds its shape longer and harder than 14K gold without thinning over time. The premium is $280 at 1/2 ct. For occasional wear, 14K gold is fine. For a pendant worn daily, the platinum upgrade is worth it.

### What chain length works best for an emerald cut diamond pendant?

16 inches sits at the collarbone — right for buyers who want a choker-adjacent look or wear lower necklines. 18 inches sits mid-decolletage and is the most common choice for an east-west pendant — it positions the horizontal stone where the step-cut light is most visible. 20 inches works for higher necklines or buyers who prefer the pendant to sit lower on the chest.

### Is the emerald cut diamond pendant available in yellow gold?

Yes. The [East-West Bezel Pendant in 14K Yellow Gold](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-14k-yellow-gold-1-2-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251426?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is available in 1/4, 1/2, 3/4, and 1 ct. sizes at the same prices as white gold across all carats. Yellow gold creates warm contrast against the step-cut's white light. The north-south solitaire pendant is also available in 14K yellow gold across the same size range.

### What is the difference between 10 CTW and 15 CTW for an emerald cut tennis necklace?

At 10 CTW, individual stones are approximately 0.29ct each — roughly 4.5mm × 3.3mm. At 15 CTW, individual stones are approximately 0.43ct each — roughly 5.2mm × 3.8mm. The per-stone size increase from 10 to 15 CTW is visible at neckline distance and creates a wider, more prominent band of step-cut light. The [10 CTW](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-tennis-necklace-with-10-ctw-emerald-cut-diamonds-in-14k-white-gold-item-297603?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is $15,750; the [15 CTW](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-tennis-necklace-with-15-ctw-emerald-cut-diamonds-in-14k-white-gold-item-297604?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is $25,893.

### Can I match an emerald cut pendant with emerald cut drop earrings?

Yes — and this pairing works especially well because both pieces use the step-cut's horizontal light direction. An east-west pendant at chest level and [emerald cut diamond earrings](/emerald-cut-diamond-earrings) at the ear create a cohesive set where the step-cut reflections echo each other. A 1/2 ct. pendant pairs naturally with 1/4 ct. drop earrings — similar stone presence at different positions on the body without competing visually.

### What is the difference between a north-south solitaire pendant and an east-west bezel pendant for everyday wear?

The east-west bezel is more practical for daily wear. The bezel covers all four corners of the stone completely, eliminating the chipping risk from daily impact and movement. The north-south solitaire uses prong settings with exposed corners — fine for occasions but less forgiving for active daily wear. At 1/2 ct., the [east-west bezel is $1,820](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-2-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251401?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and the [north-south solitaire is $1,848](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/emerald-cut-cut-diamond-solitaire-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-2-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251281?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — nearly identical in price, completely different in look and durability.

### Does the emerald cut tennis necklace work as a gift?

Yes, for someone who understands step-cut jewelry and knows what to expect. The tennis necklace does not sparkle the way a brilliant-cut version does. If the recipient expects constant glitter, they will be surprised. If they appreciate the step-cut's architectural quality, the [10 CTW at $15,750](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-tennis-necklace-with-10-ctw-emerald-cut-diamonds-in-14k-white-gold-item-297603?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is a distinctive, unusual gift in a category where most people default to round brilliant.

### What is the emerald cut diamond necklace platinum vs 14K gold price difference?

At 1/2 ct. pendant: 14K gold is [$1,820](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-2-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251401?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational), platinum is [$2,100](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-platinum-1-2-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251402?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — a $280 premium. At 1 ct.: 14K gold is [$5,190](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251407?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational), platinum is [$5,460](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-emerald-cut-bezel-diamond-pendant-in-platinum-1-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251408?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — a $270 premium. For tennis necklaces at 10 CTW: 14K gold is [$15,750](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-tennis-necklace-with-10-ctw-emerald-cut-diamonds-in-14k-white-gold-item-297603?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational), platinum is [$17,250](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/necklaces/east-west-bezel-tennis-necklace-with-10-ctw-emerald-cut-diamonds-in-platinum-item-297613?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — a $1,500 gap.

